## cc SESSION START PROCEDURE

```
1. git fetch --all
2. git merge origin/main          ← prompts always pushed to main by Janis
3. Read cc_rules.md
4. Read knowledge.map (this file)
5. Read cc_chat_log.md            ← see what Claude Web flagged last session
6. Read /prompts/[task].md        ← filename told by Janis in chat message
7. Read latest .scad for active model (see cc_chat_log.md for filename)
8. Read rules-dimensions.md + .claude/rules-materials.md (for SCAD tasks)
9. Read .claude/rules-codes.md (for SCAD tasks)
10. Read product-specific rules if prompt specifies
```

---

## COMMUNICATION FLOW

```
Janis + Claude Web → agree on goal
Claude Web → writes /prompts/[task-name].md
Janis → saves file to repo /prompts/ → git push to main
Janis → tells cc: "read prompts/[task-name].md and execute"
cc → git fetch + merge → reads prompt → executes → commits
cc → updates cc_chat_log.md with results and flags
Janis → screenshots → pastes to Claude Web
Claude Web → QA pass/fail → writes next prompt if needed
```

---

## PROMPT DELIVERY RULE (LOCKED)
- Claude Web ALWAYS delivers work as a file: /prompts/[task-name].md
- Janis saves file to repo and pushes to main branch
- cc reads file from repo — NEVER from chat text paste
- This ensures every instruction is version controlled

---

## NEVER DUPLICATE RULES FILES
- rules-dimensions.md: root only (authoritative)
- .claude/ files: .claude/ only — no root copies
- If a file exists in both places, root wins for root files, .claude/ wins for .claude/ files

